//Mass - Characterization

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from 'Contrast enhanced' in Page 03 of Cardiac MRI
And	I'm on Page 09 of Cardiac MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Mass' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization' tab is enabled and selected by default
And 'Differential diagnosis' tab is enabled

And 'Anterior mediastinum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Middle mediastinum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Posterior mediastinum' checkbox is enabled

And 'Upper mediastinum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lower mediastinum' checkbox is enabled

And 'Maximum diameter axial' input field is enabled
And 'Well defined' radio button is enabled
And 'iLL defined' radio button is enabled
And 'Infiltration' radio button is enabled

And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

And 'Signal behavior T1w' slide bar is enabled
And 'Signal behavior T2w' slide bar is enabled

And 'Fat' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cysts' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Capsule' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled

Then 'Marked' radio button is enabled
And 'Mild' radio button is enabled
And 'None' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Infiltration' radio button
Then 'Pleura' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pericardium' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bones' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'None' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
